# CarbonBlazor AI Rules

## Mission
Generate Blazor components and pages that follow IBM Carbon design principles as implemented by CarbonBlazor.

## Project Context
- This repository is a Razor Class Library plus demo and tests.
- Component source lives under `CarbonBlazor/Components/*`.
- Shared enums live in `CarbonBlazor/Enums.cs`.
- Design tokens and component classes live in `CarbonBlazor/wwwroot/carbon-blazor.css`.
- JS helpers live in `CarbonBlazor/wwwroot/carbon-blazor.js`.
- Demo pages live in `CarbonBlazor.Demo/Pages/*`.

## Required Setup For Apps
- Register CarbonBlazor services in `Program.cs`:
  - `builder.Services.AddCarbonBlazor();`
- Wrap app/page layout with `CbThemeProvider`.
- Use `CbHeader`, `CbSideNav`, and `CbContent` for shell layout in demo-like pages.

## Namespace And Imports
For demo pages/components, include:
- `@using CarbonBlazor`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Actions`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Content`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Data`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Feedback`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Forms`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Foundations`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Overlays`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Shell`
- `@using CarbonBlazor.Components.Structure`

## Component Authoring Rules
- Prefer CarbonBlazor components over raw HTML controls in demo pages.
- Use two-way binding conventions already used by the library:
  - `@bind-Value` for `Value` + `ValueChanged`
  - `@bind-Open` for overlay/nav open states
  - `@bind-SideNavOpen` in `CbHeader`
- Preserve accessibility labels:
  - Inputs should always have `Label`.
  - Icon-only actions should include accessible labels.
- Use `RenderFragment` slots (`ChildContent`, `Footer`, `Toolbar`, `NavContent`, etc.) instead of custom DOM wrappers.
- Pass through extra HTML attributes via unmatched attributes only when needed.

## Required Parameters (EditorRequired)
These are enforced and must be supplied:
- `CbIconButton.Label`
- `CbTextInput.Label`
- `CbTextArea.Label`
- `CbTreeViewNode.Node`

## CSS And Naming Conventions
- All CarbonBlazor classes use the `cb-` prefix.
- Use existing classes and variants (`cb-btn--primary`, `cb-tag--teal`, etc.).
- Do not invent a new class naming system.
- Do not hardcode colors for Carbon UI elements; rely on CSS variables.
- Token names use `--cb-*` custom properties.

## Theme Rules
- Valid themes: `White`, `G10`, `G90`, `G100`, `Teal` (`CbTheme`).
- Theme wrapper should set `data-theme` via `CbThemeProvider`.
- Dark themes (`G90`, `G100`) already define `color-scheme: dark`; do not override arbitrarily.

## Layout Rules For Demo Pages
- Follow the existing page structure:
  - Top-level heading (`h1`), short intro paragraph.
  - Sections grouped in `cb-demo-card`/grid patterns used in demo pages.
- Keep interactions keyboard-friendly and screen-reader-friendly.
- Use Carbon spacing rhythm (`--cb-spacing-*`) and avoid ad-hoc spacing values.

## Don’ts
- Do not replace Carbon components with plain `input`, `button`, or custom div-based controls unless component coverage is missing.
- Do not remove ARIA attributes from existing components.
- Do not bypass `CbThemeProvider` for theming.
- Do not create incompatible variants outside existing enums unless explicitly requested.
